%S A396534 0,1580,3636,8319,12719,18723,26939,38199,64736,90060,124820,172536,
%T A396534 238040,392579,540123,742679,1020759,1402523,2303220,3163160,4343736,
%U A396534 5964500,8189580,13439223,18451319,25332219,34778723,47747439,78344600,107557236,147662060,202720320
%N A396534 Nonnegative values x of solutions (x, y) to the Diophantine equation x^2 + (x + 79^2)^2 = y^2.
%C A396534 For the generic case x^2 + (x + p^2)^2 = y^2 with p = m^2 - 2 a (prime) number in A028871, m >= 7 (p >= 47), the first five consecutive solutions are (0, p^2), (2m^3+2m^2-4m-4, m^4+2m^3-4m-4), (4m^3+8m^2+8m, m^4+4m^3+12m^2+8m+4), (3m^4-20m^3+44m^2-40m+12, 5m^4-28m^3+60m^2-56m+20), (3m^4-10m^3+2m^2+20m-16, 5m^4-14m^3+28m-20) and the other solutions are defined by (X(n), Y(n)) = (3*X(n-5) + 2*Y(n-5) + p^2, 4*X(n-5) + 3*Y(n-5) + 2p^2).
%C A396534 X(n) = 6*X(n-5) - X(n-10) + 2p^2, and Y(n) = 6*Y(n-5) - Y(n-10) (can be easily proved using X(n) = 3*X(n-5) + 2*Y(n-5) + p^2, and Y(n) = 4*X(n-5) + 3*Y(n-5) + 2p^2).
%F A396534 a(n) = 6*a(n-5) - a(n-10) + 12482 for n >= 11; a(1)=0, a(2)=1580, a(3)=3636, a(4)=8319, a(5)=12719, a(6)=18723, a(7)=26939, a(8)=38199, a(9)=64736, a(10)=90060.
%e A396534 For p=79 (m=9) the first five (5) consecutive solutions are (0, 6241), (1580, 7979), (3636, 10525), (8319, 16769), (12719, 22831)
%Y A396534 Cf. A028871 (primes of the form m^2 - 2).
%Y A396534 Solutions x to x^2+(x+p^2)^2=y^2: A118554 (p=7), A207059 (p=17), A309998 (p=23), A331265 (p=31), A332000 (p=47), A396526 (p=71), this sequence (p=79).
%K A396534 nonn
%O A396534 1,2
